<div id="review_3665019345" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3665019345" />
    <a title="Nick Black" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/655723-nick-black"><img alt="Nick Black" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1315018121p2/655723.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3665019345?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nick Black" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nick Black" href="/user/show/655723-nick-black">Nick Black</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780375727207" href="/book/show/199170.The_Fabric_of_the_Cosmos">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/655723-nick-black?shelf=snap-crackle-pop-science">snap-crackle-pop-science</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3665019345" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer175909558440499572">it&apos;s like a smart version of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33426.Hyperspace_A_Scientific_Odyssey_Through_Parallel_Universes__Time_Warps__and_the_Tenth_Dimension' title='Hyperspace A Scientific Odyssey Through Parallel Universes, Time Warps, and the Tenth Dimension by Michio Kaku' rel='nofollow noopener'> hyperspace</a>, covering much the same range (even the straining last chapter on CTCs and teleportation), but with a real desire to instruct rather than hype. finally made clear to me several things which had escaped my understanding across a number of textbooks and probably twice as many pop books:<br/><br/>* the relationship of the higgs boson to the inflaton, and that the higgs is likely the lightest of a set of scalar bosons<br/>* the mechanisms of a big bounce<br/>* the maximum entrop</span>
  <span id="freeText175909558440499572" style="display:none">it's like a smart version of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33426.Hyperspace_A_Scientific_Odyssey_Through_Parallel_Universes__Time_Warps__and_the_Tenth_Dimension" title="Hyperspace A Scientific Odyssey Through Parallel Universes, Time Warps, and the Tenth Dimension by Michio Kaku" rel="nofollow noopener"> hyperspace</a>, covering much the same range (even the straining last chapter on CTCs and teleportation), but with a real desire to instruct rather than hype. finally made clear to me several things which had escaped my understanding across a number of textbooks and probably twice as many pop books:<br /><br />* the relationship of the higgs boson to the inflaton, and that the higgs is likely the lightest of a set of scalar bosons<br />* the mechanisms of a big bounce<br />* the maximum entropy of a planck area and the relationship to the holographic principle<br />* the principles and sources of a low-entropy early universe, as discussed at dreamier length in the great <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10638.The_Road_to_Reality_A_Complete_Guide_to_the_Laws_of_the_Universe" title="The Road to Reality A Complete Guide to the Laws of the Universe by Roger Penrose" rel="nofollow noopener"> the road to reality</a><br /><br />honestly i think i understand the electroweak higgs better from this book than any other source i've read, which seems pretty shocking. an outstanding work from professor greene.</span>
  <a data-text-id="175909558440499572" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


